by (Fatema Buhuligah)¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

This dataset includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area.

Issues¶

Quality

  • There are some missing value.
  • Unneeded columns (start_station_id, start_station_latitude, start_station_longitude, end_station_id, end_station_latitude & end_station_longitude).
  • Datatype to be changed:
    • start_time & end_time best to be datetime instead of object.
    • bike_id best to be object.
    • member_birth_year best to be intger instead of float.
  • duration_sec values best to be in minutes instead of seconds.

Tidiness

  • Generate new column for a new variable (member_age) from the member_birth_year.
  • Both start_time & end_time columns contain Multi variables.

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The dataset contains 174875 trip records in February 2019, with 17 variables:

  • bike_id
  • user_type: Subscriber or Customer
  • member_gender
  • member_birth_year
  • member_age
  • bike_share_for_all_trip: Yes or No
  • duration_min: The duration of the trip in minutes
  • start_station_name
  • end_station_name
  • start_Date
  • start_Hour
  • start_Day
  • start_Month: All of the records have February for the start month
  • end_Date
  • end_Hour
  • end_Day
  • end_Month

For the data type:

  • The duration_min is a float data type.
  • The member_birth_year, member_age, start_Hour & end_Hour are integer.
  • The start_Date & end_Date are datetime.
  • The remaining columns are string.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I'm interested in finding if the member characteristics like (the member type, gender and age) affecting the bike trips duration. Also, I would like to explore how the different time periods like (the weekdays or the hour of the day) affect the trips, and how long does the average trip take.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

user_type, member_gender & member_age will support the member characteristics. duration_min will support bike trips duration. Whereas start_Date, start_Hour, start_Day, start_Month, end_Date, end_Hour, end_Day & end_Month will support the investigation in different time periods.
